text:
Coenties Slip, east from but not including Pearl, to and including South Streets, showing the South Ferry division of the Second and Third Aves. Elevated Line winding its course from Pearl (left foreground) down Front Street (right center) to the Battery. Also seen is Jeanette Park, a quadrilaterally shaped area which divides Coenties Slip in two parts. Coenties Slip is shaped in the form of an isosceles triangle, with Pearl Street as its vertex and South Street as its base. In the background appears the East River and the Brooklyn shore, across it. Pier 7 is visible on the left.

About 1885.

(2) The same, from a slightly different angle. April 1, 1928.

P. L. Sperr.

(3) The same, showing a closer view. Notice boy ringing old fashioned hand bell (a custom adhered to at this school). May 18, 1934.

P. L. Sperr.

text:
(1)
South Street, west side, at Coenties Slip, showing Jeanette Park. Coenties Slip runs westward from South Street, on both sides of Jeanette Park and converges at Pearl Street, to form an isosceles triangle with South Street, as its base. Also shown, are some of the skyscrapers dominating the financial sector of lower Manhattan.

January 11, 1932.

P. L. Sperr.

(2)
A portion of the same, showing a closer view of the north side of Conties Slip, with the Seamen's Church Institute (extreme right), at the N.E. corner of Front Street. Also shown, is the Farmer's Loan and Trust Co. Building (background), and a "diner" of sea food, in the foreground.

April 24, 1932.

P. L. Sperr.

(3)
A portion of the same, showing the south side of Coenties Slip, west from, but not including South, to, but not including Front Streets.

June 12, 1933.

P. L. Sperr.
